<subSubSection id="4002AA866FC18A11044CD19D590F9E92" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="9C8F348876EEB210B152E47FA2B5567C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FBBFAF5041CE692C92A2D8D22BF55A6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flowering was observed in September and October. Fruiting was only observed in November, but probably extends till December.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="95ED692113A49B70A5D14131D7CC412B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9D54C2D562FF025E41C7A6D54120DF09" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="113672EF75B12C5EF7C4FF7EE0AE860F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="34415FC18957323BB175F549B4C37A7F" authorityName="Jia X. Li" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Swertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Swertia hongquanii" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hongquanii">
<emphasis id="6F8A407A61D28041B5D874AB19DC821B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Swertia hongquanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the type location in Tianmenshan National Forest Park. The climate here is cool, foggy and humid (annual rainfall ca. 1700 mm) and belongs to the subtropical monsoon climate (
<bibRefCitation id="E008DEC00EA130E5E32FC5FB8BE45701" author="Li, JX" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Tropical and Subtropical Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="573 - 576" refId="B13" refString="Li, JX, Luo, KW, Huang, HQ, Mou, C, 2008. Additions novelty to the seed plants flora of Tianmen Shan, Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province. Journal of Tropical and Subtropical Botany 16 (6): 573 - 576" title="Additions novelty to the seed plants flora of Tianmen Shan, Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province." volume="16" year="2008">Li et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E15482340A0C7CAE8C1157222CD0B1AE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0134895" author="Zhang, GJ" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B19" refString="Zhang, GJ, Hu, HH, Zhang, CF, Tian, XJ, Peng, H, Gao, TG, 2015. Inaccessible Biodiversity on Limestone Cliffs: Astertianmenshananensis (Asteraceae), a new critically endangered species from China. PLoS One 10(8): e0134895. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0134895" title="Inaccessible Biodiversity on Limestone Cliffs: Astertianmenshananensis (Asteraceae), a new critically endangered species from China. PLoS One 10 (8): e 0134895." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0134895" year="2015">Zhang et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The new species grows on the tops of steep limestone mountains surrounded by cliffs above an altitude of ca. 1400 m. The clifftops are covered by mixed evergreen-deciduous forest dominated by species of 
<taxonomicName id="3BC25C4B3165A92E0655BC30441862AE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Swertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="31504C4B0B18CF6D5FF33925AA78F7FC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Swertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lauraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B850CDC99B34FB33E92FACE94CEC6374" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Swertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA6C939CAEE0227E4EE4B0147E1D69" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aceraceae" genus="Swertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Aceraceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D256572A91E9FE6946A0E7191B35EEFA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ulmaceae" genus="Swertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ulmaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="22982D71F41D63A12F02B177E89E89A9" author="Li, JX" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Tropical and Subtropical Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="573 - 576" refId="B13" refString="Li, JX, Luo, KW, Huang, HQ, Mou, C, 2008. Additions novelty to the seed plants flora of Tianmen Shan, Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province. Journal of Tropical and Subtropical Botany 16 (6): 573 - 576" title="Additions novelty to the seed plants flora of Tianmen Shan, Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province." volume="16" year="2008">Li et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). One population occurs in the crevices of limestone cliffs; it is covered by shrubs and herbs with little soil but is rich in humus. It is accompanied by 
<taxonomicName id="475E212A4B329D0C43EE1F262A0A82A3" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Violaceae" genus="Viola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Viola davidii" order="Violales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="davidii">
<emphasis id="44482CBE299EBF32A8F142174C8E0547" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Viola davidii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Franch., 
<taxonomicName id="ADF30862935A8F21A4EBC1F6168FBB78" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Youngia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Youngia" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ADADC4EA43A5D58E21BA480E350F78C1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Youngia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cass. sp., 
<taxonomicName id="51CC7A6A4C6AD4FBEF9F7399651ED1A4" authorityName="Lecoy. ex Oliv" authorityYear="1888" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thalictrum ichangense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ichangense">
<emphasis id="F47E09908EBD6C67D0D6E5EF7B4C7440" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thalictrum ichangense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lecoy. ex Oliv., 
<taxonomicName id="2EA939D65285A285145B9A8212103C14" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aster ageratoides" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ageratoides">
<emphasis id="1EDC94000FABEE0461FEB2B83F905BFB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aster ageratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Turcz., 
<taxonomicName id="A0FA3C59AB2CD416316145E2977E12C7" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Calamagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calamagrostis arundinacea" order="Graminales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="arundinacea">
<emphasis id="DB0E86856E43E2DC2C05425406EB9D56" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Calamagrostis arundinacea</emphasis>
